9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 414, L.D. 646, “Resolve, Establishing
10 the Commission to Study Unregulated Storm Water Pollution”
11 Amend the resolve by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, Establishing the Commission to Study Unmanaged Storm Water Pollution'
13 Amend the resolve in the emergency preamble in the 2nd indented paragraph in the
14 first 2 lines (page 1, lines 3 and 4 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "How to Address
15 Unregulated" and inserting the following: 'Unmanaged'
16 Amend the resolve in section 1 in the first 2 lines (page 1, lines 12 and 13 in L.D.) by
17 striking out the following: "How to Address Unregulated" and inserting the following:
18 'Unmanaged'
19 Amend the resolve in section 2 in subsection 3 in the first line (page 1, line 22 in L.D.)
20 by striking out the following: "Two representatives of environmental or community
21 groups" and inserting the following: 'One representative of an environmental group'
22 Amend the resolve in section 2 by inserting after subsection 3 the following:
23 '4. One representative who is an engineer with expertise in the design and
24 implementation of storm water planning for development purposes, appointed by the
25 President of the Senate;'
26 Amend the resolve in section 2 in subsection 5 in the first line (page 1, line 26 in L.D.)
27 by striking out the following: "engineer or representative from a soil and water conservation
28 district" and inserting the following: 'representative of the development industry'
29 Amend the resolve in section 2 by striking out all of subsections 6 and 7 and inserting
30 the following:
31 '7. The Commissioner of Environmental Protection or the commissioner's designee;'
32 Amend the resolve in section 2 in subsection 8 in the last line (page 1, line 33 in L.D.)
33 by striking out the following: "and"
