COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 414, L.D. 646
1 Amend the resolve in section 2 in subsection 9 in the first line (page 1, line 34 in L.D.)
2 by striking out the following: "designee." and inserting the following: 'designee; and'
3 Amend the resolve in section 2 by inserting after subsection 9 the following:
4 '10. The Commissioner of Transportation or the commissioner's designee.'
5 Amend the resolve in section 2 by renumbering the subsections to read consecutively.
6 Amend the resolve in section 5 by striking out all of subsections 1 to 4 (page 2, lines
7 10 to 20 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
8 '1. Compile and review data regarding the actual and potential effects of storm water
9 pollution on public and environmental health;
10 2. Identify and develop strategies to address knowledge gaps that hinder the State's
11 ability to craft law, policy and other responses to mitigate storm water pollution;
12 3. Identify pollutants of concern that are not effectively managed through state and
13 federal storm water laws and rules, including, but not limited to, chloride pollution, and
14 recommend strategies to address those identified pollutants;
15 4. Identify and recommend strategies to address storm water pollution associated with
16 development that is not effectively managed through state and federal storm water laws
17 and rules, including through the municipal separate storm sewer system general permitting
18 process, or through other regulatory tools; and'
19 Amend the resolve in section 5 in subsection 5 in the 2nd line (page 2, line 22 in L.D.)
20 by inserting after the following: "health," the following: 'water quality,'
21 Amend the resolve by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
22 section number to read consecutively.
23 SUMMARY
2244 This amendment changes the name of the legislative study commission proposed in the
2255 resolve to the Commission to Study Unmanaged Storm Water Pollution and makes changes
2266 to the membership and duties of that commission.
2277 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2288 (See attached)
